--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/adr/ADR-0002-parallel-pure-utility-modules.md
@@ -0,0 +1,52 @@
+# ADR-0002: Three parallel-isolatable pure-utility modules in src/lib
+
+- Status: Accepted
+- Date: 2026-05-27
+- Relates to: ADR-0001 (test harness + pure-logic coverage — reused, not re-derived)
+
+## Context
+
+`src/lib` already holds pure, dependency-free helpers (`cn.ts`, `format.ts`).
+Stack: Next.js 16 / React 19 / TypeScript-strict, ESM, `moduleResolution: bundler`,
+Node v24 built-in test runner via `tsx` (the ADR-0001 harness).
+
+The request asks for three small utility surfaces. They are deliberately scoped
+**file-disjoint** — each in its own new file with its own colocated test file and
+**no cross-imports** — so they can be implemented fully in parallel worktrees and
+merged with zero conflicts. The only shared edit is `package.json` test wiring,
+which is one-time and owned by ADR-0001.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add three independent modules, each `module.ts` + `module.test.ts`, no module
+importing another:
+
+1. `slug.ts` — `slugify(text)`: lowercase → trim → collapse `[^a-z0-9]+` to a
+   single `-` → strip leading/trailing `-`. **ASCII-only by design** (accented
+   Latin folds to separators; diacritic transliteration is a separate task).
+2. `num.ts` — `clamp(value, min, max)` (inclusive; `±Infinity` snaps to a bound;
+   `NaN` value propagates; non-finite bound or `min>max` throws `RangeError`) and
+   `roundTo(value, decimals)` (exponential-notation re-parse to beat binary-FP, so
+   `roundTo(1.005,2)===1.01`; non-finite value returned unchanged; neg/NaN
+   decimals → 0).
+3. `str.ts` — `truncate(text, max, ellipsis='…')` (ellipsis counted against `max`,
+   result length ≤ `max`) and `titleCase(text)` (first char up / rest down,
+   **whitespace runs preserved**).
+
+Tests use extensionless relative imports (`./slug`) to satisfy strict `tsc`.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- +24 tests, no new framework surface beyond the single `tsx` devDependency.
+- The disjoint design is proven: parallel implement/merge is conflict-free
+  outside the lone `package.json` edit.
+- ASCII-only `slugify` degrades non-Latin input to separators — acceptable for
+  current English-locale SEO; revisit if internationalized slugs are needed.
+
+## Verification (2026-05-27)
+
+- Workspace had reset at start (no `test` script, `tsx` absent, only `cn.ts` +
+  `format.ts` in `src/lib`, only ADR-0001 doc survived). Re-implemented from this
+  settled decision.
+- `npm test` → 24 pass / 0 fail (~215 ms, Node v24.12.0).
+- `tsc --noEmit` → clean.
